entry.title: Le Mans 2014. We are ready.

media:group.media:description: Porsche belongs to Le Mans and Le Mans belongs to Porsche. We have been absent from the top class for 16 years now but never felt more at home than today. Follow us on our return to Le Mans on Saturday, June 14th, 15:00 CET at www.porsche.com/mission2014

entry.title: Porsche Le Mans #24SocialRace

media:group.media:description:
For our return to Le Mans after 16 years, Porsche will introduce #24SocialRace on June 14th; a 24-hour social media race, a worldwide first, challenging both Twitter and Weibo users; gathering 400 million of potential pilots together around one same rule: the better you'll tweet, the faster you'll go.
Go create your team on http://www.porsche.com/24socialrace and get ready for the race start.
media:group.media:title: Porsche Le Mans #24SocialRace

entry.title: Un Pit Stop Porsche sur la route du Mans

media:group.media:description:
Porsche et Esso organisent une étape symbolique sur la route du Mans avant la course des 24 Heures. Rendez-vous du 12 au 14 juin 2014 à la station Esso de Chartes-Gasville pour vivre une expérience inédite.
Plus d'informations: http://www.porsche.com/france/sportsandevents/motorsport/pitstopporsche/
Porsche and Esso team up to create a Pit Stop on the way to Le Mans and make you feel like a pilot. Meet us at Chartes-Gasville Esso gas station for a unique experience!
Combined fuel consumption in accordance with EU 5: 9.5-8.7 l/100 km; CO2-emission: 224-205 g/km
media:group.media:title: Un Pit Stop Porsche sur la route du Mans

entry.title: Porsche Leipzig. More emotions per hour.

media:group.media:description:
Porsche Leipzig is more than a production facility. It's the home of the Cayenne, Panamera and the Macan. But there's more to Porsche Leipzig than engineering excellence alone. It's also a place where you can experience the fascinating appeal of the sports car in every facet. Enter a world that inspires emotion -- whether you're collecting your new Porsche, touring the factory, taking part in an exhilarating driver training or attending an event of any size at our wide-ranging facilities. Welcome to an exciting world where the spirit of Porsche really comes alive. It's an emotion that is difficult to describe in words alone.
Find more information: http://www.porsche-leipzig.com/
*Combined fuel consumption in accordance with EU 5: 911 models: 12.4 - 8.2 l/100km; CO2 emission: 289 -194 g/km Cayman models: 8.8 -- 7.7 l/100km, CO2 emission: 206 -180 g/km Cayenne models: 11.5-7.2 l/100 km; CO2 emission: 270-189 g/km Panamera models: 10.7 -- 3.1, CO2 emission: 249 -- 71 g/km. Electricity consumption: 16.2 kWh/100 km Macan models: 9.2 - 6.1 l/100km, CO2 emission 216 -159 g/km
media:group.media:title: Porsche Leipzig. More emotions per hour.
